<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/80243014-sydney-novais"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1550371354i/80243014._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/80243014-sydney-novais">Sydney Novais</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I&apos;m assuming that was another truth Domenica chose not to tell Dalgliesh. She could have made another copy after getting a new lover. I have a key que<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I'm assuming that was another truth Domenica chose not to tell Dalgliesh. She could have made another copy after getting a new lover. I have a key question as well, but it is about Lorrimer's desk. Why would he not lock up the incriminating draft letter that Stella found at old Lorrimer's place, which she later brought to the chapel? Unless Stella had found a key to his top drawer, it doesn't seem likely him to keep it outside with all of his philosophy books.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
