        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer50707026" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13106958705032211372"> This was not my favorite of James&apos; books. The extensive cast of characters and their interconnected lives were not only confusing, but also pushed too far beyond the edge of plausible. Certainly happenstance, family ties and being in the right place at the right (or wrong) time is the keystone to most great mystery stories, but James&apos; overachievement in this area made less of her talent. James set up a story with 30+ characters, and then defaulted to creating complicated sexual histories in ord</span>
  <span id="freeText13106958705032211372" style="display:none"> This was not my favorite of James' books. The extensive cast of characters and their interconnected lives were not only confusing, but also pushed too far beyond the edge of plausible. Certainly happenstance, family ties and being in the right place at the right (or wrong) time is the keystone to most great mystery stories, but James' overachievement in this area made less of her talent. James set up a story with 30+ characters, and then defaulted to creating complicated sexual histories in order to establish connections, all the while requiring that the reader believe that all the characters live in the same area, are associated with the same laboratory, and happened to be engaged in their scandalous deeds right around the time of the murder.<br />It was a little much.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13106958705032211372" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
